description:
Cross-file bug: If lichen_lora_l2_start() fails at line 683, lichen_l2_enable(true) returns the error but leaves the module in an inconsistent state:

- link_ctx_initialized = 1 (set at line 672)
- RX callback registered (line 682)
- LoRa NOT running (start failed)

This state is problematic because:
1. TX via lichen_l2_send() will fail at is_running() check (line 507) - OK
2. But link_ctx and callback are ready for an RX thread that isn't running

If the user later retries enable(true):
1. link_ctx_initialized is already 1, so re-init is skipped (line 659)
2. callback is re-registered (harmless)
3. start() is called again

The inconsistent state isn't directly exploitable but violates the invariant that 'link_ctx_initialized implies LoRa is ready to start'. If start() fails, the enable(true) path should clean up link_ctx state to match the disabled state.

Fix: On start() failure, clear link_ctx_initialized and optionally clean up link_ctx:
  ret = lichen_lora_l2_start();
  if (ret < 0) {
    lichen_lora_l2_set_rx_callback(NULL, NULL);
    k_mutex_lock(&tx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    k_mutex_lock(&rx_mutex, K_FOREVER);
    atomic_set(&link_ctx_initialized, 0);
    lichen_link_cleanup(&link_ctx);
    k_mutex_unlock(&rx_mutex);
    k_mutex_unlock(&tx_mutex);
  }
  return ret;
